    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Trim, then cut your <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-hoisin-pork-with-sesame-greens-and-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut a large piece of<strong> tin foil </strong>and lay the <strong>halved green beans</strong> and your <strong>sweet pea pods</strong> in the middle</p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and scrunch the edges up to form a tightly sealed parcel, put the parcel on a baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 10-15 min or until cooked</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Make 2 separate parcels!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-hoisin-pork-with-sesame-greens-and-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the greens are cooking, add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>and <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 110ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[175ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[225ml]</span> cold water and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-hoisin-pork-with-sesame-greens-and-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!) and cook for 3-4 min or until browned, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-hoisin-pork-with-sesame-greens-and-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Finely slice some of your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> into rounds and set aside for garnish</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chilli</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-hoisin-pork-with-sesame-greens-and-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mince has browned, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>ginger</strong> and<strong> chopped</strong> <strong>chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add your <strong>hoisin sauce</strong>, <strong>cornflour </strong>and <strong>soy sauce </strong>with 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[75ml] </span><strong>water</strong> and cook for a further 4 min or until the sauce becomes sticky and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>spicy hoisin mince</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-hoisin-pork-with-sesame-greens-and-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the greens are done, remove the parcel[s] from the oven and drain away any excess water</p><p>Add them to a bowl with your <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong> and stir to combine \u2013 these are your <strong>sesame greens</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-hoisin-pork-with-sesame-greens-and-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spicy hoisin mince </strong>with the <strong>sesame greens</strong> over the <strong>cooked cauliflower rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>reserved chilli rounds</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
